cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with image registration using convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of anatomical labels to infer voxel-level transformation is a machine learning task, which falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with multimodal image registration, which is a sub-topic of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the use of neural networks for registration is a sub-topic of neural networks (cs.NE).
